Turns an ADM Factory JSON into an easy-to-process binning table.

admJSONFactoryToBinning.Rd

It turns the ADM Factory JSON in the exact same format as the datamart binning table which includes aggregating from the internal sub-bin model (to support individual field values) back to aggregate values.

admJSONFactoryToBinning(factoryJSON, modelname = "Dummy")

Arguments

factoryJSON

JSON string for a single model, usually the pyfactory field from the table returned by getModelsFromJSONTable.
modelname

Optional name for the model, filled in into the modelid field of the binning table.

Value

A data.table containing the flattened-out predictor binning.

Examples

if (FALSE) admFactory <- getModelsFromJSONTable(conn)
binning <- admJSONFactoryToBinning(admFactory$pyfactory[1])

#> Error in fromJSON(aFactory): object 'admFactory' not found
